**Overall Meaning:**

This verse explains that the necklace worn by Krishna represents Brahman (the ultimate reality) as understood by his mental sons (the mind). The crown on his head is described as the eternal and the form of goodness (Sattva), implying that Krishna embodies the ultimate truth and the highest quality of existence. 
